result.name: Beef & Liberty Burgers, Hong Kong International Airport

html_attributions: Beef & Liberty Burgers, Hong Kong International Airport

reviews.text:
Beef & Liberty Burgers located on the landside with decent burger, and they offer excellent view of runway.
When waiting on the door, waitress will ask for your flight time before getting in, as the burger takes long to prepare.  You can request for the window seats but you will need to wait for long.  Their window seats with nice view of runway and gate, and you can sit here for long and the staffs will not push you away.  
They offer wide range of burgers and drinks, but the burger is disappointed as its over cooked.  A good place to wait for your boarding anyway

This place was recommended to me by a frequent traveller when I said I was looking for a quiet place to work during a long layover. It's hard to find. Took me an hour and I asked several people: It is after immigration if coming in (i.e. once you are in the shopping area between the boarding gates), upstairs from the Chanel shop. There are two sections: One light, white with more bar stools where you can people-watch. The quieter section is opposite; with some darker, more hidden nooks, views of the planes, and one table with a plug point for charging (provided you have the right plug - Europe/UK I think?). The burgers are beautiful! Glossy buns, juicy meat and some local variants. Note: They don't come with chips. You can also get wine by the glass here. Staff are very polite.

Hamburger place to pass the time waited for the flight out of Hong Kong.  If you must eat here be sure to budget plenty of time as thing do take a while.
The portions are all on the small side. The burgers as simply served all lonely on the plate as fries need to be ordered separately. Perhaps they were having a bad day as the unseasoned beef patty could have have used a few grains of salt and grinds of pepper.
The service as slow and inefficient, needing multiple attempts to get the check settled.
They may deserve an other chance, but that may require another traveler.

Not too bad of a place. Thankful that is exists as I am someone who eats a more paleo style diet. Did the salmon and poached eggs without the English muffin with sweet potato fries. Not horrible, but also not the best thing ever for $20ish.

Good burgers and fries.
The burger is made of good and fresh meat cooked well.
The liberty fries are nice and crunchy and the potatoes have a good flavor.
The decoration is simple but pleasant.
The waiting time for a hamburger made to order is definitely adequate.
Strangely my neighbours had to ask four times to get the bill.
